  "sections": {
    "Description": "A giant wasp that moves through the air to attack with its stinger.",
    "Strategy": "Unlike the regular and AlphaHornets, the Hornet Leader is a lot less mobile at 3 move points instead of 5, making it much less likely to outmaneuver grounded mechs into tricky spots. However, it sports a large attacking threat range at 3 tiles, making it capable of dealing large amounts of grid damage in a single attack combined with its flying mobility. It's also more difficult to take out due to its high health; thus, it's best to whittle it down with a pushing attack that can redirect its large attack range into other enemies, then take it out in a subsequent turn.\nIn a similar vein to theAlpha Hornet, it's very helpful to deploy Mechs in tight spots and narrow chokepoints near buildings against the Hornet Leader, so that it can't occupy that tile. It can also be baited by placing at least two Mechs near it in a row, as it will prioritize attacking as many targets as possible; this eases the need to neutralize it immediately if it does not target the grid."
  },
  "full_text": "Hornet Leader\nDetails\nHealth\n6\nMove\n3\nSystems\nSuper Stinger\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nStab three tiles in a row for 2 damage each.\nSpecial\nFlying\n: Flying units can move over any terrain tile.\nHornet Leader\nis one of the Boss\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nA giant wasp that moves through the air to attack with its stinger.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nUnlike the regular and Alpha\nHornets\n, the Hornet Leader is a lot less mobile at 3 move points instead of 5, making it much less likely to outmaneuver grounded mechs into tricky spots. However, it sports a large attacking threat range at 3 tiles, making it capable of dealing large amounts of grid damage in a single attack combined with its flying mobility. It's also more difficult to take out due to its high health; thus, it's best to whittle it down with a pushing attack that can redirect its large attack range into other enemies, then take it out in a subsequent turn.\nIn a similar vein to the\nAlpha Hornet\n, it's very helpful to deploy Mechs in tight spots and narrow chokepoints near buildings against the Hornet Leader, so that it can't occupy that tile. It can also be baited by placing at least two Mechs near it in a row, as it will prioritize attacking as many targets as possible; this eases the need to neutralize it immediately if it does not target the grid.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
